{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To answer the first research question regarding the general sentiment towards Chat-GPT, we first preprocessed the texts.",
    "Following the steps in (Loureiro et al. 2022), we replaced user handles and URL links with generic placeholders, namely @user and http.",
    "Note that we neither lowercased the text nor removed emojis for this task, because they could provide sentiment information and were included for the training of sentiment analysis models we would use.",
    "We selected three sentiment analysis models that are specifically suitable for Twitter data: VADER (Hutto and Gilbert 2014), Twitter-roBERTa (Barbieri et al. 2020), and XLM-T (Barbieri et al. 2022).",
    "VADER is a lexicon-and rule-based model, while Twitter-roBERTa and XLM-T are Transformer-based models trained on tweets and fine-tuned for sentiment analysis."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Following the steps in (Loureiro et al. 2022), we replaced user handles and URL links with generic placeholders, namely @user and http.",
    "We selected three sentiment analysis models that are specifically suitable for Twitter data: VADER (Hutto and Gilbert 2014), Twitter-roBERTa (Barbieri et al. 2020), and XLM-T (Barbieri et al. 2022)."
